PROJECT TITTLE:

Developed a full-stack web application to automate and manage corporate insurance policies efficiently.
Designed and implemented the frontend using HTML, CSS, and JavaScript to provide user login, dashboard, and policy viewing features.
Built a secure backend using Java and Spring Boot, implementing RESTful APIs for policy management and user authentication.
Integrated MySQL database using Spring Data JPA to store and retrieve user and policy information.
Implemented CRUD operations for insurance policies to reduce manual processing and improve accuracy.
Followed a modular architecture separating frontend, backend, and database layers for better scalability and maintainability.
Designed the system to support future AI-based policy analysis and recommendation features.
Used GitHub for version control and collaborative development.
Project Description
The Infosys-InsurAI Corporate Policy Automation and Intelligence System is a web-based application developed to automate the management of corporate insurance policies. The system reduces manual effort by providing a centralized platform to store, manage, and analyze policy information. It enables users to log in securely, view policy details, and access insurance data through an interactive dashboard. The project is designed using modern full-stack technologies and supports future integration of AI-based policy analysis.
